[2026/05/07 12:29:30] [DEBUG] isgsa.llm: prompt content: {'Introduction': 'You are an experienced recommender systems researcher. Your previous code for research experiment had a bug, so based on the information below, you should revise it in order to fix this bug. Your response should be an implementation outline in natural language, followed by a single markdown code block which implements the bugfix/solution.', 'Research task': " You are an expert recommender systems research assistant who is looking to help the user with their requests.\nThe user has some idea and you want to conduct creative experiments to gain scientific insights.\nYour aim is to run experiments to gather sufficient results to report back to the user.\nThe idea is:\n\nď»żI'd like to run an experiment to quantify how much data split random seeds affect recommender system accuracy. Please use LensKit 0.14.4 to test three algorithms: ALS, ItemKNN, and Pop. Run this on the following three datasets with implicit feedback: MovieLens100K, Amazon Video Games, Last.FM. The raw files are stored in your working directory with the filenames u.data, VideoGames.csv, UserTaggedArtists-timestamps.dat. First, preprocess all datasets with 5-core filtering. For the Amazon and MovieLens datasets, please also convert any ratings greater than 3 to implicit interactions. Here's the main experimental procedure: Generate 5 different random seeds for data splitting. For each algorithm, dataset, and seed, please do a user-based 80/20 holdout split. Train all models using standard hyperparameters. For the analysis, I need you to measure nDCG@k and Precision@k for k=1, 5, 10 and conduct a short statistical analysis.", 'Previous (buggy) implementation': '```python\nimport os\nworking_dir = os.path.join(os.getcwd(), \'working\')\nos.makedirs(working_dir, exist_ok=True)\n\nimport time\nimport numpy as np\nimport pandas as pd\nfrom scipy import stats\nfrom sklearn.model_selection import train_test_split\nimport matplotlib.pyplot as plt\n\n# ----------------------------\n# Robust LensKit imports\n# ----------------------------\nimport lenskit\n\ntry:\n    from lenskit import topn\nexcept Exception:\n    topn = None\n\n# Data conversion helper: LensKit 0.14.4 API varies by install; avoid brittle import.\n# We will pass pandas DataFrames directly when possible, but keep a small adapter.\ndef to_lenskit_ratings(df):\n    df = df[[\'user\', \'item\', \'rating\']].copy()\n    df[\'user\'] = df[\'user\'].astype(str)\n    df[\'item\'] = df[\'item\'].astype(str)\n    df[\'rating\'] = df[\'rating\'].astype(float)\n    return df\n\n# Algorithm imports with fallbacks, prioritized for LensKit 0.14.4-like installs.\nALS = None\nItemKNN = None\nPop = None\n\nfor mod, name in [\n    (\'lenskit.algorithms.als\', \'BiasedMF\'),\n    (\'lenskit.algorithms.als\', \'ImplicitMF\'),\n    (\'lenskit.algorithms.als\', \'ALS\'),\n]:\n    try:\n        module = __import__(mod, fromlist=[name])\n        ALS = getattr(module, name)\n        break\n    except Exception:\n        pass\n\nfor mod, name in [\n    (\'lenskit.algorithms.item_knn\', \'ItemKNN\'),\n    (\'lenskit.algorithms.item_knn\', \'ItemItem\'),\n]:\n    try:\n        module = __import__(mod, fromlist=[name])\n        ItemKNN = getattr(module, name)\n        break\n    except Exception:\n        pass\n\nfor mod, name in [\n    (\'lenskit.algorithms.popular\', \'Popular\'),\n    (\'lenskit.algorithms.basic\', \'Popular\'),\n    (\'lenskit.algorithms.basic\', \'Pop\'),\n]:\n    try:\n        module = __import__(mod, fromlist=[name])\n        Pop = getattr(module, name)\n        break\n    except Exception:\n        pass\n\nnp.random.seed(42)\n\nexperiment_data = {\n    \'MovieLens100K\': {\'metrics\': {\'train\': [], \'val\': []}, \'losses\': {\'train\': [], \'val\': []}, \'predictions\': [], \'ground_truth\': [], \'seeds\': [], \'algorithms\': []},\n    \'AmazonVideoGames\': {\'metrics\': {\'train\': [], \'val\': []}, \'losses\': {\'train\': [], \'val\': []}, \'predictions\': [], \'ground_truth\': [], \'seeds\': [], \'algorithms\': []},\n    \'LastFM\': {\'metrics\': {\'train\': [], \'val\': []}, \'losses\': {\'train\': [], \'val\': []}, \'predictions\': [], \'ground_truth\': [], \'seeds\': [], \'algorithms\': []},\n}\n\n# ----------------------------\n# Dataset readers\n# ----------------------------\ndef read_movielens(path):\n    df = pd.read_csv(path, sep=\'\\t\', names=[\'user\', \'item\', \'rating\', \'timestamp\'], engine=\'python\')\n    df = df[df[\'rating\'] > 3].copy()\n    df[\'rating\'] = 1.0\n    df[\'user\'] = df[\'user\'].astype(str)\n    df[\'item\'] = df[\'item\'].astype(str)\n    return df[[\'user\', \'item\', \'rating\', \'timestamp\']]\n\n\ndef read_amazon(path):\n    df = pd.read_csv(path)\n    cols = {c.lower(): c for c in df.columns}\n    user_col = cols.get(\'reviewerid\', cols.get(\'user_id\', list(df.columns)[0]))\n    item_col = cols.get(\'asin\', cols.get(\'item_id\', cols.get(\'movieid\', list(df.columns)[1])))\n    rating_col = cols.get(\'overall\', cols.get(\'rating\', None))\n    ts_col = cols.get(\'unixreviewtime\', cols.get(\'timestamp\', None))\n    if rating_col is None:\n        df[\'rating\'] = 1.0\n    else:\n        df = df[df[rating_col] > 3].copy()\n        df[\'rating\'] = 1.0\n    df[\'timestamp\'] = df[ts_col] if ts_col is not None else np.arange(len(df))\n    df[\'user\'] = df[user_col].astype(str)\n    df[\'item\'] = df[item_col].astype(str)\n    return df[[\'user\', \'item\', \'rating\', \'timestamp\']]\n\n\ndef read_lastfm(path):\n    df = pd.read_csv(path, sep=\'\\t\', header=None, engine=\'python\')\n    if df.shape[1] >= 3:\n        df = df.iloc[:, :3]\n        df.columns = [\'user\', \'item\', \'timestamp\']\n    else:\n        raise ValueError(\'Unexpected LastFM format\')\n    df[\'rating\'] = 1.0\n    df[\'user\'] = df[\'user\'].astype(str)\n    df[\'item\'] = df[\'item\'].astype(str)\n    return df[[\'user\', \'item\', \'rating\', \'timestamp\']]\n\n\ndef five_core(df):\n    df = df.copy()\n    changed = True\n    while changed:\n        changed = False\n        uc = df[\'user\'].value_counts()\n        ic = df[\'item\'].value_counts()\n        keep = df[\'user\'].isin(uc[uc >= 5].index) & df[\'item\'].isin(ic[ic >= 5].index)\n        if keep.sum() < len(df):\n            df = df[keep].copy()\n            changed = True\n    return df.reset_index(drop=True)\n\n\ndef make_holdout(df, seed=0, test_frac=0.2):\n    rng = np.random.RandomState(seed)\n    users = df[\'user\'].unique()\n    tr_users, te_users = train_test_split(users, test_size=test_frac, random_state=rng.randint(0, 2**31 - 1))\n    train = df[df[\'user\'].isin(tr_users)].copy()\n    test = df[df[\'user\'].isin(te_users)].copy()\n    # Ensure every test user has at least one train interaction for candidate generation.\n    moved = []\n    for u, grp in test.groupby(\'user\'):\n        if len(grp) > 0:\n            moved.append(grp.iloc[[0]])\n    if moved:\n        moved_df = pd.concat(moved, ignore_index=False)\n        train = pd.concat([train, moved_df], ignore_index=True)\n        test = test.drop(index=moved_df.index, errors=\'ignore\')\n    return train.reset_index(drop=True), test.reset_index(drop=True)\n\n# ----------------------------\n# Metrics\n# ----------------------------\ndef eval_rows(rows, ks=(1, 5, 10)):\n    out = {f\'ndcg@{k}\': [] for k in ks}\n    out.update({f\'precision@{k}\': [] for k in ks})\n    for _, gt, recs in rows:\n        gt = set(gt)\n        for k in ks:\n            topk = recs[:k]\n            hits = np.array([1.0 if i in gt else 0.0 for i in topk], dtype=float)\n            out[f\'precision@{k}\'].append(float(hits.mean()) if k > 0 else 0.0)\n            dcg = float(np.sum(hits / np.log2(np.arange(2, len(hits) + 2)))) if len(hits) else 0.0\n            ideal = min(len(gt), k)\n            idcg = float(np.sum(1.0 / np.log2(np.arange(2, ideal + 2)))) if ideal > 0 else 0.0\n            out[f\'ndcg@{k}\'].append(dcg / idcg if idcg > 0 else 0.0)\n    return {m: float(np.mean(v)) for m, v in out.items()}\n\n# ----------------------------\n# Training / prediction\n# ----------------------------\ndef train_lenskit_model(name, train_df):\n    ratings = to_lenskit_ratings(train_df)\n    if name == \'ALS\':\n        if ALS is None:\n            raise ImportError(\'ALS algorithm unavailable in installed LensKit\')\n        try:\n            model = ALS(features=32, iterations=15, reg=0.1)\n        except Exception:\n            model = ALS()\n    elif name == \'ItemKNN\':\n        if ItemKNN is None:\n            raise ImportError(\'ItemKNN algorithm unavailable in installed LensKit\')\n        try:\n            model = ItemKNN(nnbrs=40)\n        except Exception:\n            model = ItemKNN()\n    else:\n        if Pop is None:\n            raise ImportError(\'Popular algorithm unavailable in installed LensKit\')\n        model = Pop()\n    # Fit with a version-robust call signature.\n    try:\n        model.fit(ratings)\n    except Exception:\n        model.fit(ratings, None)\n    return model\n\n\ndef predict_lenskit(model, train_df, test_df, kmax=10):\n    train_items = train_df.groupby(\'user\')[\'item\'].apply(set).to_dict()\n    all_items = train_df[\'item\'].astype(str).unique().tolist()\n    rows = []\n    for u, grp in test_df.groupby(\'user\'):\n        seen = train_items.get(u, set())\n        gt = set(grp[\'item\'].astype(str))\n        cand = [i for i in all_items if i not in seen]\n        rec_items = []\n        # Try multiple recommendation interfaces for LensKit variants.\n        if hasattr(model, \'recommend\'):\n            try:\n                rec = model.recommend(u, n=kmax, candidates=cand)\n                if isinstance(rec, pd.DataFrame):\n                    if \'item\' in rec.columns:\n                        rec_items = rec[\'item\'].astype(str).tolist()\n                else:\n                    rec_items = list(rec)\n            except Exception:\n                rec_items = cand[:kmax]\n        elif topn is not None and hasattr(topn, \'predict\'):  # fallback path, if available\n            rec_items = cand[:kmax]\n        else:\n            rec_items = cand[:kmax]\n        rows.append((u, gt, rec_items[:kmax]))\n    return rows\n\n\ndef fit_predict_pop(train_df, test_df, kmax=10):\n    pop = train_df[\'item\'].value_counts()\n    ranks = pop.index.astype(str).tolist()\n    train_items = train_df.groupby(\'user\')[\'item\'].apply(set).to_dict()\n    rows = []\n    for u, grp in test_df.groupby(\'user\'):\n        gt = set(grp[\'item\'].astype(str))\n        seen = train_items.get(u, set())\n        recs = [i for i in ranks if i not in seen]\n        rows.append((u, gt, recs[:kmax]))\n    return rows\n\n# ----------------------------\n# Load and preprocess data\n# ----------------------------\ndatasets = {\n    \'MovieLens100K\': read_movielens(os.path.join(os.getcwd(), \'u.data\')),\n    \'AmazonVideoGames\': read_amazon(os.path.join(os.getcwd(), \'VideoGames.csv\')),\n    \'LastFM\': read_lastfm(os.path.join(os.getcwd(), \'UserTaggedArtists-timestamps.dat\')),\n}\n\nfor ds_name, df in list(datasets.items()):\n    df = five_core(df)\n    df[\'user\'] = df[\'user\'].astype(str)\n    df[\'item\'] = df[\'item\'].astype(str)\n    datasets[ds_name] = df\n    print(f\'{ds_name}: {len(df)} interactions, {df.user.nunique()} users, {df.item.nunique()} items\')\n\n# ----------------------------\n# Experiment loop\n# ----------------------------\nseeds = [11, 22, 33, 44, 55]\nalgorithms = [\'ALS\', \'ItemKNN\', \'Pop\']\nresults = []\n\nfor ds_name, df in datasets.items():\n    for seed in seeds:\n        train_df, test_df = make_holdout(df, seed=seed, test_frac=0.2)\n        for alg in algorithms:\n            t0 = time.time()\n            try:\n                if alg == \'Pop\':\n                    rows = fit_predict_pop(train_df, test_df, kmax=10)\n                else:\n                    model = train_lenskit_model(alg, train_df)\n                    rows = predict_lenskit(model, train_df, test_df, kmax=10)\n                metrics = eval_rows(rows, ks=(1, 5, 10))\n                metrics[\'fit_time\'] = time.time() - t0\n                metrics[\'seed\'] = seed\n                metrics[\'algorithm\'] = alg\n                metrics[\'dataset\'] = ds_name\n                results.append(metrics)\n                experiment_data[ds_name][\'metrics\'][\'val\'].append(metrics)\n                experiment_data[ds_name][\'seeds\'].append(seed)\n                experiment_data[ds_name][\'algorithms\'].append(alg)\n                experiment_data[ds_name][\'predictions\'].append(rows)\n                experiment_data[ds_name][\'ground_truth\'].append(test_df[[\'user\', \'item\']].to_records(index=False))\n                print(f"{ds_name} | seed={seed} | {alg} | nDCG@10={metrics[\'ndcg@10\']:.4f} P@10={metrics[\'precision@10\']:.4f}")\n            except Exception as e:\n                print(f"{ds_name} | seed={seed} | {alg} failed: {e}")\n\nres_df = pd.DataFrame(results)\nres_path = os.path.join(working_dir, \'all_results.csv\')\nres_df.to_csv(res_path, index=False)\n\n# ----------------------------\n# Statistical analysis\n# ----------------------------\nprint(\'\\nSummary (mean ± std over seeds):\')\nfor (ds, alg), grp in res_df.groupby([\'dataset\', \'algorithm\']):\n    print(f"\\n{ds} - {alg}")\n    for m in [\'ndcg@1\', \'ndcg@5\', \'ndcg@10\', \'precision@1\', \'precision@5\', \'precision@10\']:\n        mu = grp[m].mean()\n        sd = grp[m].std(ddof=1)\n        cv = sd / mu if mu != 0 else np.nan\n        print(f\'  {m}: {mu:.4f} ± {sd:.4f} (CV={cv:.3f})\')\n\nprint(\'\\nSeed sensitivity (lower std = more stable):\')\nfor ds in res_df[\'dataset\'].unique():\n    sub = res_df[res_df[\'dataset\'] == ds]\n    for m in [\'ndcg@10\', \'precision@10\']:\n        st = sub.groupby(\'algorithm\')[m].std().sort_values()\n        print(f\'{ds} {m}: \' + \', \'.join([f\'{k}={v:.4f}\' for k, v in st.items()]))\n\n# Pairwise t-tests on nDCG@10 across algorithms, per dataset.\nprint(\'\\nPairwise t-tests on nDCG@10 (across seeds):\')\nfor ds in res_df[\'dataset\'].unique():\n    sub = res_df[res_df[\'dataset\'] == ds]\n    algs = sub[\'algorithm\'].unique().tolist()\n    for i in range(len(algs)):\n        for j in range(i + 1, len(algs)):\n            a = sub[sub[\'algorithm\'] == algs[i]][\'ndcg@10\'].values\n            b = sub[sub[\'algorithm\'] == algs[j]][\'ndcg@10\'].values\n            if len(a) == len(b) and len(a) > 1:\n                t, p = stats.ttest_rel(a, b)\n                print(f\'{ds}: {algs[i]} vs {algs[j]} -> t={t:.3f}, p={p:.4f}\')\n\n# ----------------------------\n# Save arrays / experiment data\n# ----------------------------\nnp.save(os.path.join(working_dir, \'experiment_data.npy\'), experiment_data, allow_pickle=True)\nnp.save(os.path.join(working_dir, \'results_matrix.npy\'), res_df[[\'dataset\', \'algorithm\', \'seed\', \'ndcg@1\', \'ndcg@5\', \'ndcg@10\', \'precision@1\', \'precision@5\', \'precision@10\']].to_records(index=False), allow_pickle=True)\n\n# ----------------------------\n# Plotting\n# ----------------------------\nfor metric in [\'ndcg@10\', \'precision@10\']:\n    plot_df = res_df.groupby([\'dataset\', \'algorithm\'])[metric].agg([\'mean\', \'std\']).reset_index()\n    fig, ax = plt.subplots(figsize=(10, 4))\n    x = np.arange(len(algorithms))\n    width = 0.25\n    for i, ds in enumerate(plot_df[\'dataset\'].unique()):\n        sdf = plot_df[plot_df[\'dataset\'] == ds].set_index(\'algorithm\').reindex(algorithms).reset_index()\n        ax.bar(x + i * width, sdf[\'mean\'], width=width, yerr=sdf[\'std\'], capsize=3, label=ds)\n    ax.set_xticks(x + width)\n    ax.set_xticklabels(algorithms)\n    ax.set_ylabel(metric)\n    ax.set_title(f\'{metric} by dataset and algorithm\')\n    ax.legend()\n    fig.tight_layout()\n    fig.savefig(os.path.join(working_dir, f\'{metric.replace("@", "_")}_by_dataset_algorithm.png\'), dpi=150)\n    plt.close(fig)\n\nprint(\'\\nSaved results to:\', res_path)\n\n```', 'Execution output': '```\nMovieLens100K: 54413 interactions, 938 users, 1008 items\nAmazonVideoGames: 231780 interactions, 24303 users, 10672 items\nLastFM: 173778 interactions, 1543 users, 7286 items\nNumba is using threading layer omp - consider TBB\nfound 1 potential runtime problems - see https://boi.st/lkpy-perf\nMovieLens100K | seed=11 | ALS | nDCG@10=0.0839 P@10=0.0995\nnormalized ratings are zero, centering is not recommended\nMovieLens100K | seed=11 | ItemKNN | nDCG@10=0.0839 P@10=0.0995\nMovieLens100K | seed=11 | Pop | nDCG@10=0.3638 P@10=0.3420\nMovieLens100K | seed=22 | ALS | nDCG@10=0.0940 P@10=0.1021\nnormalized ratings are zero, centering is not recommended\nMovieLens100K | seed=22 | ItemKNN | nDCG@10=0.0940 P@10=0.1021\nMovieLens100K | seed=22 | Pop | nDCG@10=0.3880 P@10=0.3612\nMovieLens100K | seed=33 | ALS | nDCG@10=0.1325 P@10=0.1399\nnormalized ratings are zero, centering is not recommended\nMovieLens100K | seed=33 | ItemKNN | nDCG@10=0.1325 P@10=0.1399\nMovieLens100K | seed=33 | Pop | nDCG@10=0.3985 P@10=0.3681\nMovieLens100K | seed=44 | ALS | nDCG@10=0.0698 P@10=0.0670\nnormalized ratings are zero, centering is not recommended\nMovieLens100K | seed=44 | ItemKNN | nDCG@10=0.0698 P@10=0.0670\nMovieLens100K | seed=44 | Pop | nDCG@10=0.3973 P@10=0.3691\nMovieLens100K | seed=55 | ALS | nDCG@10=0.1481 P@10=0.1638\nnormalized ratings are zero, centering is not recommended\nMovieLens100K | seed=55 | ItemKNN | nDCG@10=0.1481 P@10=0.1638\nMovieLens100K | seed=55 | Pop | nDCG@10=0.3903 P@10=0.3649\nAmazonVideoGames | seed=11 | ALS | nDCG@10=0.0000 P@10=0.0000\nnormalized ratings are zero, centering is not recommended\nAmazonVideoGames | seed=11 | ItemKNN | nDCG@10=0.0000 P@10=0.0000\nAmazonVideoGames | seed=11 | Pop | nDCG@10=0.0219 P@10=0.0143\nAmazonVideoGames | seed=22 | ALS | nDCG@10=0.0000 P@10=0.0000\nnormalized ratings are zero, centering is not recommended\nAm